"Usage: rhachet [options] [command]

rhachet cli interface. weave threads 🧵 of thought, stitched 🪡 with a rhachet
⚙️

Options:
  -c, --config <path>       where to find the rhachet.use.ts config
  -h, --help                display help for command

Commands:
  init [options]            initialize roles from packages or generate
                            rhachet.use.ts
  repo                      repository management commands
  roles                     manage role resources (link, init, boot, cost)
  list [options]            list available roles or skills under a role
  readme [options]          print documentation for the registry, a role, or a
                            skill
  run [options]             run a solid skill (deterministic, no brain)
  enroll [options] <brain>  enroll a brain CLI with customized roles
  choose [options]          select one attempt file, archive its peer files, and
                            remove unrelated ones
  ask [options]             invoke a skill or start a fluid conversation with an
                            actor
  act [options]             invoke a rigid skill with brain
  upgrade [options]         upgrade rhachet, role, and/or brain packages to
                            latest versions
  update                    see "upgrade"
  keyrack                   manage credentials via keyrack
  help [command]            display help for command
"
`;

